("12","1","2018-07-05 05:53:38","2018-07-05 05:53:38","<p>[vc_section][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" equal_height=\"yes\" content_placement=\"middle\" bg_type=\"image\" parallax_style=\"vcpb-default\" bg_image_new=\"id^4457|url^http://1969tigers.co.events/s/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Tiger-3blk.png|caption^null|alt^null|title^Tiger 3blk|description^null\" parallax_content=\"parallax_content_value\" parallax_content_sense=\"70\" enable_overlay=\"enable_overlay_value\" overlay_pattern=\"03.png\" css=\".vc_custom_1531033314432{border-top-width: 170px !important;padding-bottom: 130px !important;}\"][vc_column][ultimate_heading main_heading=\"In Memoriam\" main_heading_color=\"#eded10\" sub_heading_color=\"#81d742\" main_heading_font_family=\"font_family:Aladin|font_call:Aladin\" main_heading_style=\"font-weight:bold;\" main_heading_font_size=\"desktop:50px;tablet:30px;tablet_portrait:25px;mobile_landscape:20px;mobile:20px;\" sub_heading_font_size=\"desktop:24px;tablet:16px;tablet_portrait:16px;mobile_landscape:16px;mobile:16px;\" main_heading_margin=\"margin-bottom:2px;\" sub_heading_margin=\"margin-top:1px;\" sub_heading_style=\"font-weight:bold;\"]<em>Those Who Have Left Us Too Soon ...</em>[/ultimate_heading][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]Life, on this earth, is not forever . . . and sometimes friends and family are taken from us before we are ready to see them go. Their influence on our lives hold special memories that sadden us because we can no longer enjoy their company. But in our memory of them, we are encouraged and uplifted by the times that we did have--listening, looking, and being in their presence. Reflect and remember those Tigers that were a part of our lives and share if you will any moments of your time together.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" bg_type=\"bg_color\" bg_color_value=\"#eaeaea\"][vc_column][vc_masonry_grid post_type=\"gone-bfore\" max_items=\"-1\" style=\"load-more\" items_per_page=\"9\" gap=\"10\" orderby=\"modified\" order=\"ASC\" item=\"basicGrid_VerticalFlip\" btn_title=\"Show More...\" btn_style=\"classic\" btn_color=\"inverse\" grid_id=\"vc_gid:1537626839552-bb305401f5e574c1a6ca003a75076cc3-6\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][ultimate_heading main_heading=\"Testimonial\" spacer=\"line_only\" spacer_position=\"bottom\" line_height=\"1\" line_color=\"#eeee22\" main_heading_font_family=\"font_family:Allan|font_call:Allan|variant:700\" main_heading_style=\"font-style:italic;,font-weight:700;\" main_heading_font_size=\"desktop:50px;tablet:30px;tablet_portrait:30px;mobile_landscape:16px;mobile:15px;\" main_heading_margin=\"margin-top:10px;\" line_width=\"50\"][/ultimate_heading][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][ve_testimonial_container][ve_testimonial_section photo=\"4459\" title=\"Robert Alvarado\" occupation=\"Sleep Tech\" testimonial_name_color=\"#dbef21\" testimonial_occupation_color=\"#82d646\"]We spent moments of time with these classmates, so they are a part of our history.  We may have spent hours with them personally or we may have just shared a common subject in the classroom.  I can remember each of these classmates, the look in their eyes and the way they carried themselves and treated others.  Mike Morton came to my house on one occasion and we put on some old boxing gloves.  Bad outcome for me.  But a good memory just the same.  Gary Martin was a fast runner like his younger brother and seemed to exhibit an air of assuredness.  I spent time at Bill Bailey\'s home as a cub scout and enjoyed his wit and enthusiasm.  Mary Powell had a quiet, peaceful demeanor as did Nan along with her quick, questioning mind.  Mike DeMoss was one of the sharpest young men with a winning smile.  They left a mark--and a memory.[/ve_testimonial_section][ve_testimonial_section photo=\"402\" occupation=\"Professor\" testimonial_name_color=\"#dbef21\" testimonial_occupation_color=\"#82d646\"]Comments here.[/ve_testimonial_section][ve_testimonial_section photo=\"4463\" title=\"Janis Martin Smith\" occupation=\"Fellow tiger\" testimonial_name_color=\"#dbef21\" testimonial_occupation_color=\"#82d646\"]I have this very vivid memory of Gary Martin. He was such a gorgeous young man. Both of us being \"Martin\'s\", we walked together during graduation. Boy !! did we have a good time. When we sat down, the chatter started. We were wondering if we were going to actually get a diploma. My grades weren\'t anything to brag about and I seriously doubt that his was either. So we marched up and received this gigantic SEALED envelope. Sealed, licked tight with glue. I couldn\'t believe this was a silly thick, padded envelope. I wanted just one piece of paper. Instantly knowing that there was no diploma in it. I bravely smiled like a gracious \'married lady\' and marched back to my seat where Gary was ripping into his sealed envelope. We kinda fell into each other laughing with joy ( and relief) that we got our \'piece of paper\'. We had the world by the tail. I know ya\'ll were all around us. But my world was wrapped around Gary and two \' pieces of paper\'. Whatever else happened that night, I do not remember.</p>
<p>By the way, I got married about 5 weeks before we graduated so I thought I was really something. Married, graduated and ready to take on the world. I am just sorry that Gary can\'t celebrate with us.[/ve_testimonial_section][ve_testimonial_section photo=\"4464\" title=\"I can Meow!\" occupation=\"Baby tiger\" testimonial_name_color=\"#dbef21\" testimonial_occupation_color=\"#82d646\"]I like to pretend I\'m BIG.[/ve_testimonial_section][ve_testimonial_section photo=\"4458\" title=\"Trouble\" occupation=\"Master Mischiever\" testimonial_name_color=\"#dbef21\" testimonial_occupation_color=\"#82d646\"]I didn\'t do it.[/ve_testimonial_section][/ve_testimonial_container][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>
