<p><strong>How To Submit Your Story:</strong></p>
<p>(We hope to make it easy for you to provide your story, so there are many ways to do that):</p>
<p>#1 - Right here, on this page to the right(or below) is a way for you to send in what you will.  (Mind you, no one cares about spelling or being grammatically correct or have the right punctuation--its just--provide something!)  You can send text and maybe a picture or two embedded in the body of the text.</p>
<p>#2 - On your own device, computer, phone or tablet--write your story and save it locally until you get it finished.  Then, use the system here to upload a copy of your story to be published.  That is a safer way so that you do not lose your writing due to power interruptions, etc.</p>
<p>#3 - We realize that not everyone is computer saavy, so hand write (or type!) something!  Photocopy it and send it snail-mail.  You can send your story to:</p>
<p>Robert Alvarado</p>
<p>4629 Forsyth St. #552</p>
<p>Bagdad, FL 32530</p>
<p>#4 - Hand-write something and take a picture and send a picture of it, or fax it to:</p>
<p>Attn: Robert Alvarado</p>
<p>Fax: 850-494-9843   (please let me know when to expect it, this is a fax at work).</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Just write <strong>something</strong>, and we will figure out how to get it published--here! OK?</p>
<p>If you don\'t feel like writing something--at least, answer a few of the following:</p>
<p>1.  When did you become a Tiger? (What grade did you first attend?)</p>
<p>2.  If you did not graduate here, where did you move?</p>
<p>3.  Share what you did for a living, or any special places you visited, or anything that you have been passionate about.</p>
<p>(If you had about 4 hours to visit with an old friend that you had not seen in decades--what would you like to share?)</p>
<p>Your classmates want to know![/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Story Submit Requirements\" style=\"rounded\"]This is your site, so contribute!  It does not make any difference what you write, just submit something.  Most people do not know where you were from--before being a student in Benton.  Or what you have done and where life has taken you these 50 years since!  Share something that you remember or made an impression while at Benton.  Be it a few sentences or that book that you have always wanted to write--feel free to just share something--it\'s your story.</p>
<p>Now, submit words, pictures, sound bytes, videos--in any format normally used by Windows or Apple or Android.  If it is in some weird format, I may need for you to provide some details about the program that you used.  I know a good bit about computers, but I am older and move a little slower and still work for a living--so don\'t expect immediate publishing of what you send.  But participate--you can show your kids, grands and great-grands if you want--and share with them a little part of when you were their age.  It will also help your fellow classmates to know what has gone on--all these decades of time, so that if you get to come to this milestone reunion, you do not have to repeat your story multiple times.  Start today![/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Terms And Conditions (PLEASE READ!)\" style=\"rounded\" color=\"black\"]</p>
