("5017","1","2018-07-15 08:44:51","2018-07-15 08:44:51","I have this very vivid memory of Gary Martin. He was such a gorgeous young man. Both of us being \"Martin\'s\", we walked together during graduation. Boy !! did we have a good time. When we sat down, the chatter started. We were wondering if we were going to actually get a diploma. My grades weren\'t anything to brag about and I seriously doubt that his was either. So we marched up and received this gigantic SEALED envelope. Sealed, licked tight with glue. I couldn\'t believe this was a silly thick, padded envelope. I wanted just one piece of paper. Instantly knowing that there was no diploma in it. I bravely smiled like a gracious \'married lady\' and marched back to my seat where Gary was ripping into his sealed envelope. We kinda fell into each other laughing with joy ( and relief) that we got our \'piece of paper\'. We had the world by the tail. I know ya\'ll were all around us. But my world was wrapped around Gary and two \' pieces of paper\'. Whatever else happened that night, I do not remember.

By the way, I got married about 5 weeks before we graduated so I thought I was really something. Married, graduated and ready to take on the world. I am just sorry that Gary can\'t celebrate with us.

