<strong>How To Submit Your Story:</strong>

(We hope to make it easy for you to provide your story, so there are many ways to do that):

#1 - Right here, on this page to the right(or below) is a way for you to send in what you will.  (Mind you, no one cares about spelling or being grammatically correct or have the right punctuation--its just--provide something!)  You can send text and maybe a picture or two embedded in the body of the text.

#2 - On your own device, computer, phone or tablet--write your story and save it locally until you get it finished.  Then, use the system here to upload a copy of your story to be published.  That is a safer way so that you do not lose your writing due to power interruptions, etc.

#3 - We realize that not everyone is computer saavy, so hand write (or type!) something!  Photocopy it and send it snail-mail.

#4 - Hand-write something and take a picture and send a picture of it, or fax it (well, let me think about that--but, yes, if you let me know when to expect it, there is a fax at the office).

Just write something, and we will figure out how to get it published--here! OK?

If you don\'t feel like writing something--at least, answer a few of the following:

1.  When did you become a Tiger? (What grade did you first attend?)

2.  If you did not graduate here, where did you move?

3.  Share what you did for a living, or any special places you visited, or anything that you have been passionate about.

(If you had about 4 hours to visit with an old friend that you had not seen in decades--what would you like to share?)

