Now, plans are being made for us to get together in October because, Hey! it\'s been 50 years! So at that time, we will be in a room together--eating, visiting--and trying to remember and recall some of those memories--because they are a part of us. So, how do you get 40-50 people in a room and make it an effective way to share with each other? Difficult. And the time will pass and some things that you may want to share, do not happen, because of--time.

So, between right now and then, I would like to give you the opportunity to share what you desire with your classmates. You have plenty of time to do just that. I know--it sounds like an \'English\' assignment--to put together what you want to share, down in black and white. But think of the opportunity, and the time we have to \'share\' our journeys and allow our classmates to \'beforehand\' know what we have been up to all these years. It gives us a \'starting point\' when we do get together--\"Hey! I did not know you were at . . ., we were there 5 years ago\" or \"you like Harleys?\" or \"Yeah, I also got into Bonsai trees 25 years ago.\" Roger Johnson, some umpteen years ago, sent me an email regarding what had been going on in his life since school. I had never been in Roger\'s home, we did not attend the same church, we only knew each other while at school. I was honored that he chose to share with me his life (and it was one of those projects that I wanted to \'return\', in kind--but never did). Well, I am in the process of returning that honor, just for Roger, if no one else. But if we could, EACH, provide something similar--and make it available to our classmates before we get in that \'room\', just think of the time that will be saved and the wealth of what we could learn of each other.

So I am asking for you to honor, US, your classmates with a little of your life that you care to share. I know--assignment--but, no one is grading this, it will not be on \'60 Minutes\', it is just for those of us who care about you and the memories that you bring to our minds eye when we look back all these years. Think about it--write something![/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"If you EVER were a Tiger, or teacher . . .\" style=\"rounded\"]We would encourage any teachers to write &amp; share with their classmates!

