("5125","1","2018-09-22 16:29:47","2018-09-22 16:29:47","Hello, Benton Classmates of the Class of 1969!

This is Ronny Jimmerson, and the following are highlights from my last fifty years:

Upon graduation, I attended Louisiana Tech for four quarters and then transferred to Northwestern State University where I received a Bachelor of Science Degree in Electronics Engineering Technology.  In June of 1972, the month after Gwenda graduated from Benton High, Gwenda and I got married and I then finished up my degree.

I took a job at Ingalls Shipbuilding in Pascagoula, Mississippi, and worked there for around six years.  We bought our first house in Gautier, Mississippi and lived there until our first daughter, Shirilana, was born.  At Ingalls we were building Spruance Class Destroyers for the Navy, and I was an Interior Communications Supervisor and ran a Sea Trial and Test Crew for all the Interior Communications gear.

I left there and moved to Texarkana, Texas with a job as a Customer Engineer for IBM, repairing and maintaining small to medium size computers in the Texarkana area.  During my time with IBM, our second daughter, Krystyna, was born.  I only worked for them for a couple of years – I had to go to training sessions in Atlanta, Georgia regularly, and I think I figured I spent at least a quarter of my time out town in training.

I am God and family oriented, and I didn’t get married and have a family to be away from them, so I found a good job at Cooper Tire in Texarkana as an Electronics Technician troubleshooting and repairing computer controlled equipment!  Within a couple of years I moved into Management and worked in the Maintenance Department until I retired last year after having been there over 36 years!  I loved my work (which was mainly Maintenance Administration and Planning), but I also realized when it was time to leave!  During my time at Cooper, our third daughter, Elisabeth, and our son, Joseph, were born.

In June, Gwenda and I had our 46<sup>th</sup> Anniversary!  We have four great kids (three daughters and one son), and 12 grandkids.  We lived in Texarkana, Texas for a while, but 25 years ago moved to the country near Genoa, Arkansas – that’s about 18 miles southeast of Texarkana.  We have 30 acres and love the outdoors and all the country sounds (birds, wind blowing the leaves, deer in the field, etc.).

God has been the center of our lives.  We attend Northside Assembly of God Church in Texarkana, Texas (about a 30 minute drive), and are currently part of the Altar Ministry Team and Intercessory Prayer Team.   We were both ordained into the Ministry through Servanthood Ministries and then a group called Arising to Excellence.  I was Blessed to be able to do the Wedding Ceremony for our three youngest kids and renewed the vows of our oldest!  God has really been good to us and we recognize His Blessings!  We are not pastors of a Church or anything – just His disciples trying to do His will and live a life pleasing to HIM!

Well, that’s a “brief” rundown of what’s been going on in the last 50 years!  Our address is 768 MC 249, Fouke, Arkansas 71837, but we don’t really live in Fouke.  Genoa is so small that they only have a small post office and once the boxes were taken (years ago) you had to use the local mail carrier, which happened be Fouke.  Anyone west of the Genoa School get a Texarkana address, east of the school gets a Fouke address. My phone number is (870) 653-3893 (land line) and the Cell Number (which Gwenda and I both share) is (903) 276-7759.  We seldom answer calls from a number we don’t recognize, so please leave a message.

Be Blessed!

